
[1]sandy

   SAND'Y, a.

   1. Abounding with sand; full of sand; covered or sprinkled with sand;
   as a sandy desert or plain; a sandy road or soil.

   2. Consisting of sand; not firm or solid; as a sandy foundation.

   3. Of the color of sand; of a yellowish red color; as sandy hair.
